    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Are you sure you're hitting swap? Linux always uses all the available memory for disk caches. I can imagine if an app requests a huge chunk of memory at once it might overflow for a moment into the swap space before flushing out the disk cache, but this isn't something we have any say about. It's just how the Linux kernel works.\n",
